By Juliana Etebom, Abuja. | Chief Anthony .C. Ezekwugo, who is currently the managing director of the Nurnberger Group, has been awarded at the peace achievers international award for excellence in business development 2020. With Naomi and Ghana Must Go as the host, the event has been tagged one of the best of the year. He has been honoured with a number of Awards like Ohanaeze Ndigbo Great Achiever’s Award, One of the 100 Nigerians in Diaspora Organisation nominated into their 2018/2019 Global Hall of Fame, Indigenous Business Man of the Year 2018 by Indigenous Beauty Pageant. His vast wealth of experience spans real estate, investments, medical tourism, strategy and portfolio management.
In his role as the chief executive officer of Nurnberger Consulting Group, he originated and executed a number of landmark commercial real estate investment deals from start up to millions in annual income. He has also worked on a number of green and brownfield transactions covering oil and gas, power, agriculture, real estate, hospitality, medical tourism and financial services. He is a graduate of Economics and International Business from Martin Luther University in Halle-Saale, Germany and has an MBA in SME Finance and Development from the University of Leipzig Germany. He is a certified Project manager with Sigma Six Green and Black belts.
He has an Honorary Executive Doctorate in Business Administration (EDBA) in International Management. BOT member of Association of Entertainment
Practitioners in Nigeria. The certified project manager with Sigma Six Green and Black belts dedicated the award his family and all those working for the betterment of Nigeria to collaborate and work with the association.